| Chorleywood, Amersham A404\n| February 1976\n|- align=\"center\"\n|71.5\n|116.4\n| [[Watford]] [[A41 road|A41]]\n! scope=row| J19\n|{{no2}} Exit via J20 \u2013 Watford [[A41 road|A41]]\n| September 1976\n|- align=\"center\"\n|73.5\n|118.2\n| [[Hemel Hempstead]], [[Aylesbury]] A41\n! scope=row| J20\n| Hemel Hempstead, Aylesbury, Watford A41\n| August 1986\n|- align=\"center\"\n|76.3\n|122.8\n| The North, [[Luton]] & [[Luton Airport]] [[M1 motorway|M1]]\n! scope=row| J21\n| The North, Luton & Luton Airport M1\n| August 1986\n|- align=\"center\"\n|76.9\n|123.7\n| Watford [[A405 road|A405]] <br />[[Harrow, London|Harrow]] (M1 South)\n! scope=row| J21A\n| [[St Albans]] A405 <br />London (NW & C) (M1 (South))\n| August 1986\n|- align=\"center\"\n|80.6\n|129.7\n| London Colney [[A1081 road|A1081]]\n! scope=row| J22\n| St Albans A1081\n| August 1986\n|- align=\"center\"\n|83.3\n|134.0\n| [[Hatfield, Hertfordshire|Hatfield]] [[A1(M) motorway|A1(M)]], London (NW & C) [[A1 road (Great Britain)|A1]], [[Chipping Barnet|Barnet]] [[A1081 road|A1081]]<br />[[South Mimms services]]\n! scope=row| J23\n| Hatfield A1(M), London (NW & C) A1, Barnet A1081<br />[[South Mimms services]]\n| August 1986 (westbound)<br/>September 1975 (eastbound)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|85.9\n|138.2\n| [[Potters Bar]] [[A111 road (England)|A111]]\n! scope=row| J24\n| Potters Bar A111\n| September 1975 (westbound)<br/>June 1981 (eastbound)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|91.4\n|147.1\n| [[Enfield Town]], [[Hertford]] [[A10 road (England)|A10]]\n! scope=row| J25\n| Enfield, Hertford, [[London]] (N & C) A10\n| June 1981 (westbound)<br/>January 1984 (eastbound)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|94.9\n|152.7\n| [[Waltham Abbey (town)|Waltham Abbey]], [[Loughton]] [[A121 road (England)|A121]]\n! scope=row| J26\n| Waltham Abbey, Loughton A121\n| January 1984\n|- align=\"center\"\n|99.2\n|159.7\n| London (NE & C), [[Stansted Airport]], [[Harlow]], [[Cambridge]] [[M11 motorway|M11]]\n! scope=row| J27\n| [[London]] (NE & C) [[M11 motorway|M11(N)]], Stansted Airport, Harlow, Cambridge [[M11 motorway|M11(S)]]\n| January 1984 (westbound)<br/>April 1983 (eastbound)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|107.1\n|172.4\n| [[Chelmsford]], [[Witham]], [[Colchester]] [[A12 road (Great Britain)|A12]] <br />[[Brentwood, Essex|Brentwood]] [[A1023 road|A1023]] \n! scope=row| J28\n| Chelmsford, [[Romford]] A12 <br />Brentwood A1023\n| April 1983\n|- align=\"center\"\n|109.9\n|176.8\n| Romford, [[Basildon]], [[Southend]] [[A127 road|A127]]\n! scope=row| J29\n| Basildon, Southend, [[Romford]] A127\n| April 1983 (northbound)<br/>December 1982 (southbound)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|115.2\n|185.4\n| Tilbury, Thurrock, Lakeside A13(E), London (E & C) [[A13 road (Great Britain)|A13(W)]]<br /> [[Thurrock services]]\n! scope=row| J30\n| [[London]] (E & C), [[Barking, London|Barking]], [[Tilbury]], [[Basildon]], [[Dagenham]], [[Rainham, London|Rainham]] [[A13 road (Great Britain)|A13]]\n| December 1982\n|- align=\"center\"\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"00703C\" style=\"color: #FFD200;font-size:120%;\"\n| colspan=\"6\" | A282 (Dartford Crossing)\n|- align=\"center\"\n|115.9\n|186.6\n|{{no2}} Exit via J30 \u2013 [[Purfleet]] (A1090), [[South Ockendon]], [[Thurrock services]] A1306\n! scope=row| J31\n| [[Thurrock]] ([[Lakeside Shopping Centre|Lakeside]]), Thurrock services [[A1306 road|A1306]], [[Purfleet]] ([[A1090 road|A1090]]), [[West Thurrock]] ([[A126 road|A126]])\n| December 1982\n|- align=\"center\"\n|\n|\n|style=\"background:#dcdcfe;\"| [[Dartford Crossing]] South<br>(Queen Elizabeth II Bridge)<br>[[File:UK traffic sign symbol NS67.svg|40px]]\n! scope=row| [[River Thames|River<br />Thames]]\n|style=\"background:#dcdcfe;\"| Dartford Crossing North<br>(Dartford Tunnels)<br>[[File:UK traffic sign symbol NS67.svg|40px]]\n| November 1963 (west tunnel)<br>May 1980 (east tunnel)<br>October 1991 (bridge)\n|-\n|colspan=6|'''Notes'''\n*Distances in kilometres and carriageway identifiers are obtained from [[driver location signs]]/location marker posts. Where a junction spans several hundred metres and the data is available, both the start and finish values for the junction are shown.\n|-\n{{jctbtm|keys=incomplete,toll}}\n\n==References==\n'''Notes'''\n{{notelist}}\n\n'''Citations'''\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n'''Sources'''\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|first=Wayne|last=Asher|title=Rings Around London: Orbital motorways and the battle for homes before roads|publisher=Capital History|year=2018|isbn=978-1854144218|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Baldwin|first=Peter|last2=Bridle|first2=Ron|last3=Baldwin|first3=Robert|last4=Porter|first4=John|title=The Motorway Achievement, Volume 1|publisher=Thomas Telford|year=2002|isbn=978-0-727-73196-8|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bramley|first=J. F.|title=Roads for Britain: a digest of plans of future highways|edition=2nd|publisher=Staples Press|year=1946|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hamilton|first=Ray|title=M25: A Circular Tour of the London Orbital|publisher=Summersdale Publishers|year=2015|isbn=978-1-783-72656-1|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=Joe|last=Moran|title=On Roads : A Hidden History|publisher=Profile Books|year=2009|isbn=978-1-846-68052-6|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Smith|first=Denis|title=London and the Thames Valley|publisher=Thomas Telford|year=2001|isbn=978-0-727-72876-0|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|author=United Nations Economic Commission for Europe |date=1 November 2016 |title=ECE/TRANS/SC.1/2016/3/Rev.1: European Agreement on Main International Traffic Arteries |url=https://www.unece.org/fileadmin/DAM/trans/doc/2016/sc1/ECE-TRANS-SC1-2016-03-Rev1e.pdf|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Citation |authorlink=Iain Sinclair |first=Iain |last=Sinclair |title=London Orbital: A Walk Around the M25 |year=2002 |location=London |publisher=Granta Books |isbn=1-86207-547-6|ref=none }}.\n*{{Citation |authorlink=Roy Phippen |first=Roy |last=Phippen |title=Travelling M25 Clockwise |year=2005 |location=London |publisher=Pallas Athene |isbn=1-873429-90-8|ref=